article.headline: Penn St. 68, Minnesota 63
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. -- Talor Battle scored 21 points and converted a steal into a key three-point play as Penn State snapped a three-game losing streak with a 68-63 win Saturday over Minnesota. Battle scored seven during a 10-0 run that turned a three-point deficit into a 63-56 lead with 26 seconds left. Freshman Devoe Joseph had a career-high 23 points to lead the Golden Gophers (19-6, 7-6 Big Ten). Battle swiped the ball in backcourt from Joseph, then raced down court for an off-balance layup to put Penn State (18-8, 7-6) up four with 57 seconds left. Battle missed the ensuing foul shot, but teammate Andrew Jones retrieved the rebound to save the possession. Battle was fouled again and hit both free throws to put the Nittany Lions up 62-56 with 37 seconds left. Stanley Pringle scored 13 points for Penn State, while Al Nolen added 10 for Minnesota.
